  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provide safe drinking water in saline areas using solar power</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Govt and NGOs have been implementing PSFs to treat surface water. Water from surface water is pumped through sand filters that work on the principal of &quot;slow sand filter&quot; on a constant flow, which creates biological film on sand layers, formed through a constant flow that removes harmful bacteria. Without constant flow of water bacteria remains and causes water borne disease. Using 12 -solar powered pond sand filters we will provide safe clean drinking water to 12,465 people. Project is funded by SOJ &amp; SOJ. The project will be implemented by Banchte Shekha in Khulna and Satkhira districts.</narrative>
  </description>
